53. Yarkoni, T. Neurosynth Core Tools v0.3.1. ZENODO; 2014.
54•. Amso D, Haas S, McShane L, Badre D. Working memory updating and the development of ruleguided behavior. Cognition. 2014; 133(1):201–210. Development confers an increasing capacity to engage in reasoning on the basis of complex hierarchical rules. This study identifies the primary developmental benefit between the ages of 7–10 and 12–30 is linked to the demands on working memory updating that is imposed by these rules, rather than the demands they impose on resolving competition. Socio-economic status was also found to predict greater age-related gains in rule-guided behavior. [PubMed: 25044248]
55. Podell JE, Sambataro F, Murty VP, Emery MR, Tong Y, Das S, Goldberg TE, Weinberger DR, Mattay VS. Neurophysiological correlates of age-related changes in working memory updating. Neuroimage. 2012; 62:2151–2160. [PubMed: 22659476]
